==German==
==Etymology==
Literally meaning "midweek", from [[mit]] "mid" and [[Woch]] "week".
===Proper noun===
'''Mittwoch''' ''m''
#[[Wednesday]], the day following [[Tuesday]] and preceeding [[Thursday]]. In German Mittwoch follows [[Dienstag]] and preceeds [[Donnerstag]].
#:''Mittwochs gehe ich immer schwimmen''

